  "prompt": "Which is correct, \"queue the music\" or \"cue the music,\" and why?",
  "response": "The correct phrase is \"cue the music.\" \n\n\"Cue the music\" means to signal or prompt someone to begin playing music, often used in the context of performances, broadcasts, or events where timing and coordination are important.\n\nOn the other hand, \"queue\" refers to lining up or arranging items in a sequence. While you could \"queue\" a playlist or arrange songs to be played in order, the idiomatic expression specifically referring to signaling the start of music is \"cue the music.\"",
